The paper proposes a new method for shortest-path distance queries on large-scale networks, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The method is specifically designed to handle social networks and web graphs, which are examples of social computing (cs.SOC) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of bitwise operations, which is a technique commonly used in computer science and information theory (cs.SI).
